gatekeep and sometimes enable--

00:02:40.670 --> 00:02:42.500
and I think it's
important to understand

00:02:42.500 --> 00:02:45.110
the sort of dialectic
relationship there--

00:02:45.110 --> 00:02:47.840
that enable citizenship
and the experiences

00:02:47.840 --> 00:02:51.590
of people encountering
some of those structures.

00:02:51.590 --> 00:02:54.470
We might quickly think
a bit about-- what

00:02:54.470 --> 00:02:55.970
we want to do here,
I think, is take

00:02:55.970 --> 00:02:58.670
three of the central
master narratives that

00:02:58.670 --> 00:03:01.610
show up in American history
and then sort of diffuse

00:03:01.610 --> 00:03:02.210
out from that.

00:03:02.210 --> 00:03:05.200
And that would be the story
of conquest concerning

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:06.200
American Indian people--

00:03:06.200 --> 00:03:08.040
Indigenous people;
the story of slavery,

00:03:08.040 --> 00:03:10.040
concerning African and
African descendant people

00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:13.280
and Indigenous people as
well; and then immigration

00:03:13.280 --> 00:03:15.560
and the ways in which
immigration, as we know,

00:03:15.560 --> 00:03:18.770
plays into all of these kinds
of economic sorts of questions.

00:03:18.770 --> 00:03:21.042
So we might imagine a
set of legislative acts

00:03:21.042 --> 00:03:23.000
that sort of structure
how we think about this.

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:25.490
For me, this always begins
with the three-fifths clause.

00:03:28.200 --> 00:03:29.930
I poll my students
every semester,

00:03:29.930 --> 00:03:32.360
and they happily tell me
it's all about three-fifths

00:03:32.360 --> 00:03:34.518
of an enslaved
person for purposes

00:03:34.518 --> 00:03:35.810
of proportional representation.

00:03:35.810 --> 00:03:38.227
What they almost always miss
is the other clause in there,

00:03:38.227 --> 00:03:40.580
Indians not taxed,
which establishes

00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:42.470
a certain kind of
ground for Native people

00:03:42.470 --> 00:03:44.900
to be in the Constitution
as being excluded

00:03:44.900 --> 00:03:47.240
from the Constitution
and setting up

00:03:47.240 --> 00:03:50.150
the sort of baseline,
or the grounding,

00:03:50.150 --> 00:03:52.370
within the American
constitutional system

00:03:52.370 --> 00:03:55.550
to imagine Indian people as
discrete and separate political

00:03:55.550 --> 00:03:58.220
entities who might leave those
entities behind and become

00:03:58.220 --> 00:04:00.682
members of the American polity.

00:04:00.682 --> 00:04:02.390
So from there, we
might imagine, thinking

00:04:02.390 --> 00:04:04.490
